Mind manipulation. Murder. Sexual assault. These are just some ingredients in Brad Meltzer's epic 7-part comic series titled Identity Crisis. When one of their own is targeted and killed how can the Justice League ensure it will never happen again? Join us as we tackle this controversial series, 20 years after the first issue was published and see whether or not the story was a polarizing as we remember. Do the themes Meltzer manages to bring up hold up? Listen in and find out! Please leave us a review on [ITunes](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us wherever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our merchandise! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by ComicBook Clique, the only stop for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.

